OL,3,C'It's transformative': Hard-of-hearing
OL,4,Ccinema goers try glasses with subtitles
OL,6,FGlasses with personalised subtitles
OL,7,Fhave been described as a potential
OL,8,Fgame-changer for people with hearing
OL,9,Floss.
OL,11,FWatchword smart glasses are designed
OL,12,Fto be worn over normal glasses and
OL,13,Falongside hearing aids and cochlear
OL,14,Fimplant processors.
OL,16,FThe captions appear on the glasses
OL,17,Flens, rather than on the big screen,
OL,18,Fmaking it possible for the individual
OL,19,Fwearer to watch the film and read the
OL,20,Fcaptions using their own personalised
OL,21,Fdevice.
